President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump traveled to Brussels, Belgium for the NATO Summit. They met with European Council President Donald Tusk and European Commission President Jean-Claude Juncker to discuss shared challenges in fighting global terrorism. President Trump also had a working lunch with President Emmanuel Macron of France, urging him to meet the NATO defense spending pledge and focus on counterterrorism. President Trump participated in the unveiling of the Article 5 and Berlin Wall memorials, expressing appreciation for contributions from the 9/11 Memorial and Museum and Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany. He also met with King Philippe and Queen Mathilde of Belgium, discussing better economic relations. Lastly, President Trump met with Prime Minister Charles Michel of Belgium to discuss defense spending and cooperation in countering ISIS. He expressed a desire for a productive economic and security relationship with Europe.